rest_of_day_open: The next two days will be a little bit stressful as I tidy up some assignments for university. After that though, I'm in the clear in terms of workload. I'm inclined to think I'll feel guilty for not doing many productive things, but at least at this point in time I think I need the break a little bit.
critical_positive: We were close enough in age gap and cultural similarities where we could talk openly and very easily. This contrasted pretty heavily to my previous three conversations where my partners definitely felt older and maturer than me, and I felt pressured to act more polite than I would in actuality.
critical_negative: At the beginning I didn't really know what kind of interests she had, so I had to assume we had nothing in common. If I had known this information beforehand, our conversation would have started a lot stronger and we probably would have been able to cover topics and make better use of the time overall.

rest_of_day_open: I think it will be ok. Since the COVID- 19 stuff started every week almost feels the same. I have tomorrow off of work, so I plan on cooking and relaxing for the day. I have my first OCD treatment therapy on Wednesday, so I am a bit nervous for that.
critical_positive: I can't remember his name, eek. But he was very self assured and led the conversation in the beginning. He seemed like he really knew what he was doing, as this was his 4th conversation. He was very pleasant and kept the conversation going. He was very knowledgeable and had a lot of interests.
critical_negative: Sometimes he would go on for a long time when he was talking and I didn't really have a chance to respond to what he was saying. And there was one long pause where I didn't know what to say. And sometimes I psych myself out and think that i am not saying anything interesting or good enough, or that i have to be perfect when i am speaking, so they think i am smart.
